30
00:03:46,580 --> 00:03:49,020
SPEAKER_10: Come often. You're always welcome.

78
00:08:19,420 --> 00:08:20,819
SPEAKER_10: Can't rush these things.

79
00:08:21,060 --> 00:08:25,089
SPEAKER_10: Fengxia's growing up. Another's on the way.

124
00:13:45,279 --> 00:13:48,149
SPEAKER_10: It's all in order, I'll be going.

125
00:13:49,919 --> 00:13:54,379
SPEAKER_10: Master Fugui, don't think badly of me...

126
00:13:54,860 --> 00:13:56,950
SPEAKER_10: for leaving you homeless.

127
00:13:57,960 --> 00:14:00,590
SPEAKER_10: But I sure like that mansion of yours.

128
00:14:00,899 --> 00:14:03,230
SPEAKER_10: See you there in a few days.

130
00:14:07,740 --> 00:14:10,330
SPEAKER_10: The game's not over yet!

131
00:14:10,409 --> 00:14:12,710
SPEAKER_10: Master Fugui, I'm sorry...

132
00:14:12,779 --> 00:14:15,769
SPEAKER_10: but you've nothing left.
What would you wager?

133
00:14:16,110 --> 00:14:18,809
SPEAKER_10: If you're unhappy, talk to Mr. Xie.

146
00:15:03,730 --> 00:15:06,529
SPEAKER_10: We'll formalize the transfer in a few days...

150
00:15:14,840 --> 00:15:15,929
SPEAKER_10: Okay?

225
00:24:01,299 --> 00:24:03,960
SPEAKER_10: A rare visitor indeed.

226
00:24:04,400 --> 00:24:07,099
SPEAKER_10: Master Fugui! It's been a year at least.

231
00:24:19,420 --> 00:24:22,009
SPEAKER_10: I've given up the puppet troupe.

232
00:24:22,119 --> 00:24:23,519
SPEAKER_10: Have a seat.

233
00:24:25,619 --> 00:24:28,990
SPEAKER_10: I don't gamble anymore.
Don't want to end up like you.

243
00:25:14,200 --> 00:25:16,190
SPEAKER_10: Earn your money yourself.

244
00:25:17,539 --> 00:25:19,529
SPEAKER_10: Put together a troupe.

343
00:42:59,670 --> 00:43:01,190
SPEAKER_10: It's your daddy.

344
00:43:06,980 --> 00:43:08,440
SPEAKER_10: What are you doing?

345
00:43:10,280 --> 00:43:11,769
SPEAKER_10: Where's mommy?

485
00:56:50,159 --> 00:56:51,530
SPEAKER_10: Enough?

486
00:56:51,699 --> 00:56:54,690
SPEAKER_10: Still not enough? Okay, I'll fill it right up.

487
00:56:56,039 --> 00:56:58,269
SPEAKER_10: Big ambition for a little kid.

488
00:56:59,570 --> 00:57:01,539
SPEAKER_10: It's more than enough.

489
00:57:01,840 --> 00:57:04,570
SPEAKER_10: So gobble away. Help yourself to sauces.

490
00:57:10,480 --> 00:57:13,010
SPEAKER_10: Youqing, I'll help you stir that up.

680
01:19:29,960 --> 01:19:31,689
SPEAKER_10: I had only one son!

802
01:30:07,500 --> 01:30:11,300
SPEAKER_10: I just caught them on a ladder,
pulling off roof tiles.

898
01:40:13,100 --> 01:40:14,470
SPEAKER_10: Come on in!

911
01:41:19,399 --> 01:41:21,489
SPEAKER_10: No wonder there's a bottle!

912
01:41:22,140 --> 01:41:23,329
SPEAKER_10: Really?

953
01:44:15,539 --> 01:44:16,640
SPEAKER_10: Who?

954
01:44:16,710 --> 01:44:18,039
SPEAKER_10: Chunsheng.

955
01:44:23,149 --> 01:44:24,779
SPEAKER_10: What do you want?

956
01:44:26,949 --> 01:44:28,850
SPEAKER_10: Come out for a second.

977
01:46:12,989 --> 01:46:15,460
SPEAKER_10: Don't go getting any stupid ideas.

978
01:46:17,729 --> 01:46:20,170
SPEAKER_10: You must bear it, no matter what!

979
01:46:21,000 --> 01:46:23,470
SPEAKER_10: You can't take that road yourself.

980
01:46:27,039 --> 01:46:29,270
SPEAKER_10: I don't want to live anymore!

981
01:46:30,539 --> 01:46:32,010
SPEAKER_10: You just have to!

982
01:46:33,850 --> 01:46:36,649
SPEAKER_10: We've been through the valley of death.

983
01:46:36,720 --> 01:46:38,949
SPEAKER_10: Coming out alive wasn't easy.

1085
01:53:49,579 --> 01:53:51,909
SPEAKER_10: I wouldn't dare.

1146
01:59:03,060 --> 01:59:04,260
SPEAKER_10: It's a boy.

